com.unimelb.swen30006.mailroom

Interface SortingStrategy

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleSortingStrategy

    public interface SortingStrategy
    An interface that defines the decisions that need to be made for a mail sorting machine. Different mail sorting machines will require different strategies, but by using the common strategy interface, they can drastically change their behaviour without needing to change their core programming

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String assignStorage(MailItem item, MailStorage storage)
      Assign an identifier for a mail item and a given storage system.

    • Method Detail

      • assignStorage

        java.lang.String assignStorage(MailItem item,
                               MailStorage storage)
                        throws MailOverflowException
        Assign an identifier for a mail item and a given storage system. Will provide immutable mail storage object to determine the identifier for the storage box to use. If no storage boxes are available to store the item, throws a MailOverflowException to indicate the sorting machine must wait until more deliveries are made before sorting more items
        Parameters:
        item - the item being sorted
        storage - the storage system in use
        Returns:
        the identifier of the assigned storage box
        Throws:
        MailOverflowException - if there are no spaces remaining for new boxes
